    "description": "This adds the ability for the user to specify an observed redshift for the AbsorptionSpectrum analysis module.  This means that when you generate a spectrum, you can see how it would look if the observer were sitting at any arbitrary redshift.  By default, this is set to z=0, so all backwards compatibility is retained.\r\n\r\nUPDATE1: Modularizing the redshift calculation to be its own method so it doesn't get looped on.  Thanks, @xarthisius .\r\n\r\nUPDATE2: Clearing merge conflicts.",
